insistent /ɪnˈsɪstənt/

1. ADJ Someone who is insistent keeps insisting that a particular thing should be done or is the case. 坚持的; 坚决的 

例： Stalin was insistent that the war would be won and lost in the machine shops. 斯大林坚持认为，战争输赢将取决于这些机械厂。 

2. insistently ADV 坚决地 [ADV with v] 

例： 'What is it?' his wife asked again, gently but insistently. “这是什么？”他妻子再次问道，语气温和但很坚决。 

3. ADJ An insistent noise or rhythm keeps going on for a long time and holds your attention. (声音、节奏等) 持续的 

例： ...the insistent rhythms of the Caribbean and Latin America. …不停息的加勒比和拉丁美洲的音乐节奏。

